late pre-bomb time (AD 1900–1960) have been precisely dated at a high temporal resolution. In this time interval, 14 C ages of all the samples dated were younger than those derived from the atmo-spheric calibration curve, apparently due to the effect of integration. Evidently, the determination of calendar ages based on 14 C dating of single peat samples from that interval may be affected by a serious error if the possibility of integration is ignored.},
