n soil. Stump harvesting would thus markedly reduce preferred habitats for these taxa. It is also possible that some species generally considered as soil animals might be occasionally dependent on stumps for, e.g. egg-laying and hatching. For such species, stump harvesting would be more detrimental than indicated by this population survey. {\textcopyright} 2012 Elsevier B.V.},
